    for i in range(n):
        nums.append(int(input()))

    print(*nums)

main()

def remove_duplicates(a, n):
    if n == 0 or n == 1:
        return n
    temp = [0] * n
    j = 0
    for i in range(0, n-1):
        if a[i] != a[i+1]:
            temp[j] = a[i]
            j += 1
    temp[j] = a[n-1]
    j += 1
    for i in range(0, j):
        a[i] = temp[i]
    return j
